headlines.description: — Miles Bridges had 26 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists and the Charlotte Hornets defeated the Utah Jazz 110-106 on Monday night to snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miles Bridges scores 26 as Hornets beat Jazz 110-106 to snap 5-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Aaron Nesmith scored 17 of his 24 points in the second half, Obi Toppin added 19 and the Indiana Pacers rallied from a 16-point deficit in the second half to beat the Sacramento Kings 111-109 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers come from 16 points down in the second half to beat the Kings 111-109

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard and Norman Powell each scored 21 points, Ivica Zubac added 18 points and 20 rebounds and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Orlando Magic 96-87 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, Powell and Zubac power the Clippers to a 96-87 win over the Magic

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 28 points and 12 rebounds, Tyler Herro added 27 points and the Miami Heat rolled past the Washington Wizards 120-94 on Monday night for their fifth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat win 5th straight, getting 55 from Herro and Adebayo to roll past Wizards 120-94

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 25 points and 14 rebounds, Al Horford scored 26 points and the Boston Celtics swept a six-game road trip for the first time in franchise history with a 117-103 win over the Memphis Grizzlies on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics beat Grizzlies 117-103 and complete the first 6-0 trip in franchise history

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 27 points and 12 assists in just 27 minutes, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rolled to a 145-117 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Monday night for their 10th straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder rout Bulls 145-117 for 10th straight win, improve to 28-1 vs the East

headlines.description: — Keon Johnson scored 24 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Dallas Mavericks 113-109 on Monday night to win consecutive games for the first time since the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets beat Mavericks 113-109 to win consecutive games for the first time since the All-Star break

events.name: Houston Rockets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 20 points and nine assists, and Gabe Vincent added 20 points on six 3-pointers in the Los Angeles Lakers’ 104-98 victory over the Houston Rockets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers hold off Rockets 104-98 with 6 3-pointers apiece from Dorian Finney-Smith, Gabe Vincent
